PowerCLI Command Remediation:
# Retrieve each TPM-mode host's configuration-encryption recovery key and store the output
# in a secured, off-host secret store. Do NOT write the key to a plaintext file the host can reach.
foreach ($h in Get-VMHost) {
    $e = Get-EsxCli -VMHost $h -V2
    if ($e.system.settings.encryption.get.Invoke().Mode -eq "TPM") {
        $rk = $e.system.settings.encryption.recovery.list.Invoke()
        [pscustomobject]@{ Host = $h.Name; RecoveryID = $rk.RecoveryID; Key = $rk.Key }
    }
}

Configuration Parameter:
Set via the NSX policy API:

PUT https://<nsx-mgr>/policy/api/v1/infra/global-config

Request body:
{
  "fips": {
    "lb_fips_enabled": true
  },
  "resource_type": "GlobalConfig",
  "_revision": <current>
}

For existing load balancers, detach and reattach each instance from its Tier-1 gateway in the NSX UI under Networking > Load Balancing.

Capture the output from the check GET command and update the TLS 1.1 protocol to false.

